item.title: Home
item.content:encoded:
Benvenuto! Join us for the most fun a Gondolier will ever have (outside of Venice)!

 

US Gondola Nationals 2018 will be hosted in the heart of Providence, Rhode Island by La Gondola Providence from November 9-11th.

An opportunity to meet fellow Gondoliers from across the nation, and participate in single and tandem races along the Providence River Walk. Preview our event schedule, and take a look at past winners. 

Amazing chance to row during Providence's WaterFire event!

All photography provided by Greg Mohr.

  

WaterFire

Providence's popular WaterFires bring visitors from across the nation and around the world to experience these events. We are excited to offer this opportunity to row in the incredible ambiance to all visiting gondoliers who are interested in doing so. Come and row in an atmosphere unlike any other in the world.

item.title: Events
item.content:encoded:
US GONDOLA NATIONALS 2018

This Year's US Gondola Nationals will be hosted by La Gondola Providence, Inc. The convention will take place form November 9th through the 11th in the heart of Rhode Island and all of our events will be around the Providence River. 

 

OVERVIEW

  • Social events for fellow Gondoliers to mix and mingle

  • Many races, including distance, sprint, and slalom

  • Incredible opportunity to row during Providence's last Waterfire of the season

  • Awards banquet to commemorate the races

  • Welcome to all Gondoliers and friends and family

  • For travelers; the nearest airport is (PVD)

  

EVENTS SCHEDULE

FRIDAY

NOV 9

Social Event

Friday Evening we will be having a social event at Union Station Brewery at 36 Exchange Terrace, Providence, RI 02903. This is the PVD Gondolier hang-out location.

 

SATURDAY

NOV 10

Races and Waterfire

Races will be held from late Saturday morning until late afternoon.

(click for detailed schedule)

5-11pm Waterfire Event.
Visiting Gondoliers are given the opportunity to row with one of our local gondoliers during the season's last Waterfire event. The theme for this fire is a Salute to Veterans for Veteran's Day Weekend. Catered food and beverages will also be provided.

 

SUNDAY

NOV 11

RACES AND AWARDS

Races held from late Sunday morning until the late afternoon.

(click for detailed schedule)

Awards Banquet to ensue after the races Sunday evening.
